44:{"block_id": "B044", "document_id": "0001047469-15-004989", "ordinal": 44, "start_line": 1838, "end_line": 1843, "raw_text": "March 27, 2014, at the direction of our board of directors, BofA Merrill Lynch distributed a first round process letter, which informed potential buyers that non-binding\npreliminary indications of interest would be due no later than April 14, 2014. Over the next few weeks, BofA Merrill Lynch, at the direction of our board of directors, continued communications\nwith potential buyers to assess interest in a potential transaction and provide information, and the Company's management continued to meet\nwith prospective buyers. In all, twenty-five potential buyers informed us that they were not interested in pursuing a potential transaction and declined to enter into a confidentiality agreement with\nus, and twenty-five potential buyers executed confidentiality agreements with us, received a copy of the marketing materials and/or met with the Company's management. While New Mountain Capital\nreceived the marketing materials and the first round process letter, it decided at the time not to submit a preliminary indication of interest.", "clean_text": "March 27, 2014, at the direction of our board of directors, BofA Merrill Lynch distributed a first round process letter, which informed potential buyers that non-binding preliminary indications of interest would be due no later than April 14, 2014. Over the next few weeks, BofA Merrill Lynch, at the direction of our board of directors, continued communications with potential buyers to assess interest in a potential transaction and provide information, and the Company's management continued to meet with prospective buyers. In all, twenty-five potential buyers informed us that they were not interested in pursuing a potential transaction and declined to enter into a confidentiality agreement with us, and twenty-five potential buyers executed confidentiality agreements with us, received a copy of the marketing materials and/or met with the Company's management. While New Mountain Capital received the marketing materials and the first round process letter, it decided at the time not to submit a preliminary indication of interest.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "March 27, 2014", "normalized": "2014-03-27", "precision": "exact_day"}, {"raw_text": "April 14, 2014", "normalized": "2014-04-14", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "NEW MOUNTAIN CAPITAL", "entity_type": "acquirer"}, {"raw_text": "the Company", "entity_type": "party_alias"}], "evidence_density": 4, "temporal_phase": "outcome"}
46:{"block_id": "B046", "document_id": "0001047469-15-004989", "ordinal": 46, "start_line": 1846, "end_line": 1848, "raw_text": "April 14, 2014, five parties, comprising four financial buyers and one strategic buyer, submitted preliminary and non-binding indications of interest. The bids received in the\npreliminary indications of interest ranged from $20.00 per share to $22.00 per share. The Board Representatives reviewed the indications of interest as well as recent progress in the potential sale\nprocess.", "clean_text": "April 14, 2014, five parties, comprising four financial buyers and one strategic buyer, submitted preliminary and non-binding indications of interest. The bids received in the preliminary indications of interest ranged from $20.00 per share to $22.00 per share. The Board Representatives reviewed the indications of interest as well as recent progress in the potential sale process.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "April 14, 2014", "normalized": "2014-04-14", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "The Board", "entity_type": "party_alias"}], "evidence_density": 3, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
48:{"block_id": "B048", "document_id": "0001047469-15-004989", "ordinal": 48, "start_line": 1851, "end_line": 1853, "raw_text": "April 16, 2014, our board of directors held a meeting in which members of the Company's management, representatives of BofA Merrill Lynch and King & Spalding joined, to\nreview the preliminary indications of interest and the potential sale process. Our board of directors reviewed the five preliminary indications of interest that had been received. After further\ndiscussion, our board of directors determined to continue the process with the parties who had submitted preliminary indications of interest.", "clean_text": "April 16, 2014, our board of directors held a meeting in which members of the Company's management, representatives of BofA Merrill Lynch and King & Spalding joined, to review the preliminary indications of interest and the potential sale process. Our board of directors reviewed the five preliminary indications of interest that had been received. After further discussion, our board of directors determined to continue the process with the parties who had submitted preliminary indications of interest.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "April 16, 2014", "normalized": "2014-04-16", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "the Company", "entity_type": "party_alias"}], "evidence_density": 2, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
50:{"block_id": "B050", "document_id": "0001047469-15-004989", "ordinal": 50, "start_line": 1856, "end_line": 1858, "raw_text": "the next few weeks, the Company's management gathered information that was to be included in the electronic data room and held internal meetings to prepare for in-depth management\npresentations with the interested parties. Moreover, two additional parties, comprising one financial party (\"Party X\") and one strategic party (\"Party Y\"), contacted representatives of BofA Merrill\nLynch on an unsolicited basis to inquire about the process.", "clean_text": "the next few weeks, the Company's management gathered information that was to be included in the electronic data room and held internal meetings to prepare for in-depth management presentations with the interested parties. Moreover, two additional parties, comprising one financial party (\"Party X\") and one strategic party (\"Party Y\"), contacted representatives of BofA Merrill Lynch on an unsolicited basis to inquire about the process.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "Party X", "entity_type": "party_alias"}, {"raw_text": "Party Y", "entity_type": "party_alias"}, {"raw_text": "the Company", "entity_type": "party_alias"}], "evidence_density": 2, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
52:{"block_id": "B052", "document_id": "0001047469-15-004989", "ordinal": 52, "start_line": 1861, "end_line": 1863, "raw_text": "May 7, 2014, access to an electronic data room containing diligence materials was made available to the five parties who submitted preliminary indications of interest to that\npoint and these parties engaged in extensive due diligence investigations of our business. As part of this process, in the first half of May 2014, the Company's management met with certain of these\nparties and provided presentations to them about our business.", "clean_text": "May 7, 2014, access to an electronic data room containing diligence materials was made available to the five parties who submitted preliminary indications of interest to that point and these parties engaged in extensive due diligence investigations of our business. As part of this process, in the first half of May 2014, the Company's management met with certain of these parties and provided presentations to them about our business.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "May 7, 2014", "normalized": "2014-05-07", "precision": "exact_day"}, {"raw_text": "May 2014", "normalized": "2014-05-01", "precision": "month"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "the Company", "entity_type": "party_alias"}], "evidence_density": 2, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
54:{"block_id": "B054", "document_id": "0001047469-15-004989", "ordinal": 54, "start_line": 1866, "end_line": 1867, "raw_text": "May 9, 2014, Party X submitted a preliminary and non-binding indication of interest to BofA Merrill Lynch, increasing the number of preliminary indications of interest received\nby us as of such date to six. The bid submitted by Party X ranged from $21.50 to $23.00 per share. However, on", "clean_text": "May 9, 2014, Party X submitted a preliminary and non-binding indication of interest to BofA Merrill Lynch, increasing the number of preliminary indications of interest received by us as of such date to six. The bid submitted by Party X ranged from $21.50 to $23.00 per share. However, on", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "May 9, 2014", "normalized": "2014-05-09", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "Party X", "entity_type": "party_alias"}], "evidence_density": 3, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
56:{"block_id": "B056", "document_id": "0001047469-15-004989", "ordinal": 56, "start_line": 1872, "end_line": 1874, "raw_text": "May 14,\n2014, prior to receiving access to the electronic data room or meeting with the Company's management, Party X informed representatives of BofA Merrill Lynch that it was no longer\ninterested in pursuing a potential transaction with the Company.", "clean_text": "May 14, 2014, prior to receiving access to the electronic data room or meeting with the Company's management, Party X informed representatives of BofA Merrill Lynch that it was no longer interested in pursuing a potential transaction with the Company.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "May 14, 2014", "normalized": "2014-05-14", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "Party X", "entity_type": "party_alias"}, {"raw_text": "the Company", "entity_type": "party_alias"}], "evidence_density": 2, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
58:{"block_id": "B058", "document_id": "0001047469-15-004989", "ordinal": 58, "start_line": 1877, "end_line": 1879, "raw_text": "May 20, 2014, Party Y submitted a preliminary and non-binding indication of interest, bringing the total number of preliminary indications of interest received by us to seven.\nThe indication of interest submitted by Party Y ranged from $19.50 to $20.50 per share. Access to the electronic data room was subsequently made available to Party Y and the Company's management met\nwith Party Y and provided a presentation about our business.", "clean_text": "May 20, 2014, Party Y submitted a preliminary and non-binding indication of interest, bringing the total number of preliminary indications of interest received by us to seven. The indication of interest submitted by Party Y ranged from $19.50 to $20.50 per share. Access to the electronic data room was subsequently made available to Party Y and the Company's management met with Party Y and provided a presentation about our business.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "May 20, 2014", "normalized": "2014-05-20", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "Party Y", "entity_type": "party_alias"}, {"raw_text": "the Company", "entity_type": "party_alias"}], "evidence_density": 3, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
60:{"block_id": "B060", "document_id": "0001047469-15-004989", "ordinal": 60, "start_line": 1882, "end_line": 1883, "raw_text": "May 22, 2014, a draft of the merger agreement was distributed to the six remaining bidders (Party X having withdrawn from the process on May 14, 2014) that had submitted\npreliminary indications of interest.", "clean_text": "May 22, 2014, a draft of the merger agreement was distributed to the six remaining bidders (Party X having withdrawn from the process on May 14, 2014) that had submitted preliminary indications of interest.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "May 22, 2014", "normalized": "2014-05-22", "precision": "exact_day"}, {"raw_text": "May 14, 2014", "normalized": "2014-05-14", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "Party X", "entity_type": "party_alias"}], "evidence_density": 3, "temporal_phase": "outcome"}
62:{"block_id": "B062", "document_id": "0001047469-15-004989", "ordinal": 62, "start_line": 1886, "end_line": 1887, "raw_text": "May 23, 2014, there was a fire at our aerosol manufacturing facility in Marietta, Georgia. The fire, and its impact on our business, added significant uncertainty to our\non-going discussions with the interested parties.", "clean_text": "May 23, 2014, there was a fire at our aerosol manufacturing facility in Marietta, Georgia. The fire, and its impact on our business, added significant uncertainty to our on-going discussions with the interested parties.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "May 23, 2014", "normalized": "2014-05-23", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [], "evidence_density": 0, "temporal_phase": "other"}
64:{"block_id": "B064", "document_id": "0001047469-15-004989", "ordinal": 64, "start_line": 1890, "end_line": 1892, "raw_text": "the next few weeks, five of the remaining six interested parties communicated to representatives of BofA Merrill Lynch that they were unable to proceed with the process due to\nconcerns regarding valuation and, in some cases, the interested parties' own internal initiatives and strategic priorities. The sixth remaining interested party declined to respond to BofA Merrill\nLynch's communications regarding a potential transaction.", "clean_text": "the next few weeks, five of the remaining six interested parties communicated to representatives of BofA Merrill Lynch that they were unable to proceed with the process due to concerns regarding valuation and, in some cases, the interested parties' own internal initiatives and strategic priorities. The sixth remaining interested party declined to respond to BofA Merrill Lynch's communications regarding a potential transaction.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [], "entity_mentions": [], "evidence_density": 1, "temporal_phase": "initiation"}
66:{"block_id": "B066", "document_id": "0001047469-15-004989", "ordinal": 66, "start_line": 1895, "end_line": 1902, "raw_text": "June 19, 2014, the Board Representatives held a meeting which included other members of our board of directors, the Company's management and representatives from BofA Merrill\nLynch and King & Spalding. The Board Representatives and other members of our board of directors were informed that each of the seven parties that submitted a preliminary indication of interest\nhad expressed concerns regarding valuation and believed that they could not pay the prices indicated in their preliminary indications of interest. During this meeting, the Board Representatives\nconsidered that five of the remaining six interested parties had communicated that they were unable to proceed with the process due to concerns regarding valuation and, in some cases, the interested\nparties' own internal initiatives and strategic priorities and that a sixth interested party was no longer responding to BofA Merrill Lynch's communications regarding a potential transaction. The\nBoard Representatives also considered that, based upon BofA Merrill Lynch's discussions with the interested parties, the interested parties recognized the opportunity to achieve potential cost\nsavings, but the complexity and nature of these potential cost savings and the requisite related investments made the interested parties unwilling to give us full credit for these potential cost\nsavings in their valuations.", "clean_text": "June 19, 2014, the Board Representatives held a meeting which included other members of our board of directors, the Company's management and representatives from BofA Merrill Lynch and King & Spalding. The Board Representatives and other members of our board of directors were informed that each of the seven parties that submitted a preliminary indication of interest had expressed concerns regarding valuation and believed that they could not pay the prices indicated in their preliminary indications of interest. During this meeting, the Board Representatives considered that five of the remaining six interested parties had communicated that they were unable to proceed with the process due to concerns regarding valuation and, in some cases, the interested parties' own internal initiatives and strategic priorities and that a sixth interested party was no longer responding to BofA Merrill Lynch's communications regarding a potential transaction. The Board Representatives also considered that, based upon BofA Merrill Lynch's discussions with the interested parties, the interested parties recognized the opportunity to achieve potential cost savings, but the complexity and nature of these potential cost savings and the requisite related investments made the interested parties unwilling to give us full credit for these potential cost savings in their valuations.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "June 19, 2014", "normalized": "2014-06-19", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "the Company", "entity_type": "party_alias"}, {"raw_text": "the Board", "entity_type": "party_alias"}], "evidence_density": 2, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
68:{"block_id": "B068", "document_id": "0001047469-15-004989", "ordinal": 68, "start_line": 1905, "end_line": 1907, "raw_text": "a June 26, 2014 meeting of our board of directors, based on the lack of buyer interest and the uncertainty surrounding the impact of the fire at our aerosol manufacturing\nfacility in Marietta, Georgia, our board of directors decided to terminate the process to explore potential strategic alternatives at that time and to continue to focus on our business and financial\nperformance.", "clean_text": "a June 26, 2014 meeting of our board of directors, based on the lack of buyer interest and the uncertainty surrounding the impact of the fire at our aerosol manufacturing facility in Marietta, Georgia, our board of directors decided to terminate the process to explore potential strategic alternatives at that time and to continue to focus on our business and financial performance.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "June 26, 2014", "normalized": "2014-06-26", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [], "evidence_density": 2, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
70:{"block_id": "B070", "document_id": "0001047469-15-004989", "ordinal": 70, "start_line": 1910, "end_line": 1915, "raw_text": "the process conducted during the first half of 2014, given that all of the parties that had signed confidentiality agreements had abandoned or withdrawn from the process, our\nboard of directors authorized letters to be delivered to those parties waiving the \"don't ask to waive\" provisions in their respective confidentiality agreements, and permitting those parties to make\nconfidential proposals to acquire the Company. As a result, following the termination of the process, no party was subject to a \"don't ask to waive\" provision or prohibited from making confidential\nacquisition proposals to the board of directors of the Company. After the termination of the 2014 potential sale process and prior to the signing of the merger agreement with New Mountain Capital, we\ndid not receive any inquiries or proposals to acquire the Company (other than from New Mountain Capital as further described below), but instead received occasional inquiries from third parties\nregarding our interest in their providing minority PIPE (\"private investment in public equity\") financing.", "clean_text": "the process conducted during the first half of 2014, given that all of the parties that had signed confidentiality agreements had abandoned or withdrawn from the process, our board of directors authorized letters to be delivered to those parties waiving the \"don't ask to waive\" provisions in their respective confidentiality agreements, and permitting those parties to make confidential proposals to acquire the Company. As a result, following the termination of the process, no party was subject to a \"don't ask to waive\" provision or prohibited from making confidential acquisition proposals to the board of directors of the Company. After the termination of the 2014 potential sale process and prior to the signing of the merger agreement with New Mountain Capital, we did not receive any inquiries or proposals to acquire the Company (other than from New Mountain Capital as further described below), but instead received occasional inquiries from third parties regarding our interest in their providing minority PIPE (\"private investment in public equity\") financing.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "NEW MOUNTAIN CAPITAL", "entity_type": "acquirer"}, {"raw_text": "the Company", "entity_type": "party_alias"}, {"raw_text": "the board", "entity_type": "party_alias"}], "evidence_density": 3, "temporal_phase": "outcome"}
73:{"block_id": "B073", "document_id": "0001047469-15-004989", "ordinal": 73, "start_line": 1921, "end_line": 1922, "raw_text": "the second half of 2014, our board of directors and management focused on our business and our Company's business plan, including addressing the impact on our aerosol business,\ncompleting our fiscal year 2015 plan and focusing on fiscal year 2014 performance.", "clean_text": "the second half of 2014, our board of directors and management focused on our business and our Company's business plan, including addressing the impact on our aerosol business, completing our fiscal year 2015 plan and focusing on fiscal year 2014 performance.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [], "entity_mentions": [], "evidence_density": 0, "temporal_phase": "other"}
75:{"block_id": "B075", "document_id": "0001047469-15-004989", "ordinal": 75, "start_line": 1925, "end_line": 1928, "raw_text": "early February 2015, New Mountain Capital contacted representatives of BofA Merrill Lynch and requested a meeting. On February 10, 2015, New Mountain Capital met with\nrepresentatives of BofA Merrill Lynch and expressed its interest in discussions with the Company regarding a potential transaction. On February 19, 2015, New Mountain Capital delivered an\nunsolicited indication of interest to the Company to acquire us for a per share price of $19.25. The indication of interest was supported by a highly confident financing letter from Jefferies\nFinance LLC, contained a request for a forty-five day exclusivity period and contemplated a \"go-shop\" period following the signing of any definitive merger agreement.", "clean_text": "early February 2015, New Mountain Capital contacted representatives of BofA Merrill Lynch and requested a meeting. On February 10, 2015, New Mountain Capital met with representatives of BofA Merrill Lynch and expressed its interest in discussions with the Company regarding a potential transaction. On February 19, 2015, New Mountain Capital delivered an unsolicited indication of interest to the Company to acquire us for a per share price of $19.25. The indication of interest was supported by a highly confident financing letter from Jefferies Finance LLC, contained a request for a forty-five day exclusivity period and contemplated a \"go-shop\" period following the signing of any definitive merger agreement.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "early February 2015", "normalized": "2015-02-05", "precision": "month_early"}, {"raw_text": "February 10, 2015", "normalized": "2015-02-10", "precision": "exact_day"}, {"raw_text": "February 19, 2015", "normalized": "2015-02-19", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "NEW MOUNTAIN CAPITAL", "entity_type": "acquirer"}, {"raw_text": "the Company", "entity_type": "party_alias"}], "evidence_density": 5, "temporal_phase": "outcome"}
77:{"block_id": "B077", "document_id": "0001047469-15-004989", "ordinal": 77, "start_line": 1931, "end_line": 1939, "raw_text": "February 23, 2015, our board of directors, together with representatives of BofA Merrill Lynch and King & Spalding, met to discuss New Mountain Capital's indication of\ninterest. Our board of directors discussed the indication of interest, including the proposed per share price, the request for exclusivity and the offer to include a \"go shop\" provision in any\ndefinitive merger agreement. Our board of directors reviewed and discussed the advantages and disadvantages of various potential alternatives, including continuing to operate on a standalone basis and\ninvesting in a supply chain transformation project, pursuing a potential transaction with New Mountain Capital on an exclusive basis combined with a \"go-shop\" provision in the merger agreement,\ncontacting a select group of potential buyers, and\nconducting a broad process to explore a potential sale of the Company. As part of these discussions, our board of directors reviewed the impact and distractions on our business associated with the\n2014 potential sale process and emphasized the importance of limiting any distractions that might be associated with pursuing another potential sale of the Company. After further discussion, our board\nof directors concluded that it would consider granting New Mountain Capital a thirty day exclusivity period if New Mountain Capital raised its offer price and confirmed that a \"go-shop\" provision\nwould be included in any potential definitive merger agreement.", "clean_text": "February 23, 2015, our board of directors, together with representatives of BofA Merrill Lynch and King & Spalding, met to discuss New Mountain Capital's indication of interest. Our board of directors discussed the indication of interest, including the proposed per share price, the request for exclusivity and the offer to include a \"go shop\" provision in any definitive merger agreement. Our board of directors reviewed and discussed the advantages and disadvantages of various potential alternatives, including continuing to operate on a standalone basis and investing in a supply chain transformation project, pursuing a potential transaction with New Mountain Capital on an exclusive basis combined with a \"go-shop\" provision in the merger agreement, contacting a select group of potential buyers, and conducting a broad process to explore a potential sale of the Company. As part of these discussions, our board of directors reviewed the impact and distractions on our business associated with the 2014 potential sale process and emphasized the importance of limiting any distractions that might be associated with pursuing another potential sale of the Company. After further discussion, our board of directors concluded that it would consider granting New Mountain Capital a thirty day exclusivity period if New Mountain Capital raised its offer price and confirmed that a \"go-shop\" provision would be included in any potential definitive merger agreement.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "February 23, 2015", "normalized": "2015-02-23", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "NEW MOUNTAIN CAPITAL", "entity_type": "acquirer"}, {"raw_text": "the Company", "entity_type": "party_alias"}], "evidence_density": 4, "temporal_phase": "outcome"}
79:{"block_id": "B079", "document_id": "0001047469-15-004989", "ordinal": 79, "start_line": 1942, "end_line": 1946, "raw_text": "February 24, 2015, at the direction of our board of directors, representatives of BofA Merrill Lynch communicated to New Mountain Capital that our board of directors might be\nwilling to consider granting New Mountain Capital a thirty day exclusivity period if New Mountain Capital raised its offer price and confirmed that a \"go-shop\" provision would be included in any\npotential definitive merger agreement. On February 26, 2015, New Mountain Capital delivered a revised indication of interest reflecting an increased per share price of $20.05, and indicated\nthat this was the highest price it was willing to offer. As part of its submission of the revised indication of interest, New Mountain Capital again requested a forty-five day exclusivity period (and\ncontemplated a countersignature by the Company), and reiterated that it would be willing to accept a \"go-shop\" provision in any definitive merger agreement.", "clean_text": "February 24, 2015, at the direction of our board of directors, representatives of BofA Merrill Lynch communicated to New Mountain Capital that our board of directors might be willing to consider granting New Mountain Capital a thirty day exclusivity period if New Mountain Capital raised its offer price and confirmed that a \"go-shop\" provision would be included in any potential definitive merger agreement. On February 26, 2015, New Mountain Capital delivered a revised indication of interest reflecting an increased per share price of $20.05, and indicated that this was the highest price it was willing to offer. As part of its submission of the revised indication of interest, New Mountain Capital again requested a forty-five day exclusivity period (and contemplated a countersignature by the Company), and reiterated that it would be willing to accept a \"go-shop\" provision in any definitive merger agreement.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "February 24, 2015", "normalized": "2015-02-24", "precision": "exact_day"}, {"raw_text": "February 26, 2015", "normalized": "2015-02-26", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "NEW MOUNTAIN CAPITAL", "entity_type": "acquirer"}, {"raw_text": "the Company", "entity_type": "party_alias"}], "evidence_density": 5, "temporal_phase": "outcome"}
81:{"block_id": "B081", "document_id": "0001047469-15-004989", "ordinal": 81, "start_line": 1949, "end_line": 1955, "raw_text": "February 26, 2015, our board of directors met, together with representatives of BofA Merrill Lynch and King & Spalding, to review New Mountain Capital's revised\nindication of interest. Our board of directors discussed and considered the fact that New Mountain Capital was not prepared to move forward in its evaluation of a potential transaction with us without\nan exclusivity agreement. Our board of directors also considered the fact that New Mountain Capital was unwilling to further increase its indicative price above $20.05 per share at this time. Our\nboard of directors discussed at length the potential strategic alternatives available to the Company, including remaining as a standalone company. Our board of directors also considered again the\nimportance of limiting any distractions that might be associated with pursuing another potential sale of the Company. After further deliberation regarding the potential advantages and disadvantages of\na sale of the Company and consideration of the opportunities and risks associated with remaining a standalone company, our board of directors determined to move forward with negotiations with New\nMountain Capital regarding the proposed sale of the Company. In view of the increased offer price, the commitment by New Mountain Capital to", "clean_text": "February 26, 2015, our board of directors met, together with representatives of BofA Merrill Lynch and King & Spalding, to review New Mountain Capital's revised indication of interest. Our board of directors discussed and considered the fact that New Mountain Capital was not prepared to move forward in its evaluation of a potential transaction with us without an exclusivity agreement. Our board of directors also considered the fact that New Mountain Capital was unwilling to further increase its indicative price above $20.05 per share at this time. Our board of directors discussed at length the potential strategic alternatives available to the Company, including remaining as a standalone company. Our board of directors also considered again the importance of limiting any distractions that might be associated with pursuing another potential sale of the Company. After further deliberation regarding the potential advantages and disadvantages of a sale of the Company and consideration of the opportunities and risks associated with remaining a standalone company, our board of directors determined to move forward with negotiations with New Mountain Capital regarding the proposed sale of the Company. In view of the increased offer price, the commitment by New Mountain Capital to", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "February 26, 2015", "normalized": "2015-02-26", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "NEW MOUNTAIN CAPITAL", "entity_type": "acquirer"}, {"raw_text": "the Company", "entity_type": "party_alias"}], "evidence_density": 4, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
83:{"block_id": "B083", "document_id": "0001047469-15-004989", "ordinal": 83, "start_line": 1960, "end_line": 1963, "raw_text": "include\na \"go-shop\" provision in any potential definitive merger agreement and the other considerations described above, our board of directors determined that it would be willing to offer to New\nMountain Capital an exclusivity period of approximately thirty days. Our board of directors also determined not to form a transaction committee because the full board would remain actively\ninvolved in overseeing the negotiations with New Mountain Capital.", "clean_text": "include a \"go-shop\" provision in any potential definitive merger agreement and the other considerations described above, our board of directors determined that it would be willing to offer to New Mountain Capital an exclusivity period of approximately thirty days. Our board of directors also determined not to form a transaction committee because the full board would remain actively involved in overseeing the negotiations with New Mountain Capital.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "NEW MOUNTAIN CAPITAL", "entity_type": "acquirer"}, {"raw_text": "transaction committee", "entity_type": "committee"}], "evidence_density": 3, "temporal_phase": "outcome"}
85:{"block_id": "B085", "document_id": "0001047469-15-004989", "ordinal": 85, "start_line": 1966, "end_line": 1967, "raw_text": "February 27, 2015, we signed an agreement with New Mountain Capital extending the term of the confidentiality provision, the \"standstill\" provision and the employee\nnon-solicitation provision in our original confidentiality agreement with them as well as providing for an exclusivity period with New Mountain Capital through March 31, 2015.", "clean_text": "February 27, 2015, we signed an agreement with New Mountain Capital extending the term of the confidentiality provision, the \"standstill\" provision and the employee non-solicitation provision in our original confidentiality agreement with them as well as providing for an exclusivity period with New Mountain Capital through March 31, 2015.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "February 27, 2015", "normalized": "2015-02-27", "precision": "exact_day"}, {"raw_text": "March 31, 2015", "normalized": "2015-03-31", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "NEW MOUNTAIN CAPITAL", "entity_type": "acquirer"}], "evidence_density": 2, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
87:{"block_id": "B087", "document_id": "0001047469-15-004989", "ordinal": 87, "start_line": 1970, "end_line": 1973, "raw_text": "March 2, 2015, we granted New Mountain Capital access to the electronic data room that had been populated with due diligence documentation during the 2014 potential sale\nprocess. Pursuant to the instruction of our board of directors, BofA Merrill Lynch asked New Mountain Capital to confirm its offer price after reviewing the due diligence materials. Over the next few\nweeks, New Mountain Capital requested additional information, and the Company's management provided this information and updated the electronic data room in response to these requests. New Mountain\nCapital and their representatives and advisors reviewed the contents of the electronic data room, including our fiscal year 2015 plan and an updated fiscal year 2015 forecast.", "clean_text": "March 2, 2015, we granted New Mountain Capital access to the electronic data room that had been populated with due diligence documentation during the 2014 potential sale process. Pursuant to the instruction of our board of directors, BofA Merrill Lynch asked New Mountain Capital to confirm its offer price after reviewing the due diligence materials. Over the next few weeks, New Mountain Capital requested additional information, and the Company's management provided this information and updated the electronic data room in response to these requests. New Mountain Capital and their representatives and advisors reviewed the contents of the electronic data room, including our fiscal year 2015 plan and an updated fiscal year 2015 forecast.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "March 2, 2015", "normalized": "2015-03-02", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "NEW MOUNTAIN CAPITAL", "entity_type": "acquirer"}, {"raw_text": "the Company", "entity_type": "party_alias"}], "evidence_density": 3, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
89:{"block_id": "B089", "document_id": "0001047469-15-004989", "ordinal": 89, "start_line": 1976, "end_line": 1978, "raw_text": "March 2015, the Company's management (including Mr. Morgan) participated in various in-person due diligence meetings with New Mountain Capital and hosted New Mountain\nCapital on multiple site visits to the Company's facilities. During these meetings, the Company's management discussed with New Mountain various aspects of our business and prospects, including our\nbusiness plan and potential initiatives.", "clean_text": "March 2015, the Company's management (including Mr. Morgan) participated in various in-person due diligence meetings with New Mountain Capital and hosted New Mountain Capital on multiple site visits to the Company's facilities. During these meetings, the Company's management discussed with New Mountain various aspects of our business and prospects, including our business plan and potential initiatives.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "March 2015", "normalized": "2015-03-01", "precision": "month"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "NEW MOUNTAIN CAPITAL", "entity_type": "acquirer"}, {"raw_text": "the Company", "entity_type": "party_alias"}], "evidence_density": 3, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
91:{"block_id": "B091", "document_id": "0001047469-15-004989", "ordinal": 91, "start_line": 1981, "end_line": 1983, "raw_text": "March 13, 2015, New Mountain Capital communicated that the $20.05 per share offer price was New Mountain Capital's \"best and final\" offer. New Mountain Capital also indicated a\nwillingness to work expeditiously towards the signing of a definitive merger agreement by April 15, 2015 and requested an extension of its exclusivity period through that date. Subsequently, on\nMarch 15, 2015, New Mountain Capital indicated that it would accelerate its due diligence process and requested that the exclusivity period be extended through April 7, 2015.", "clean_text": "March 13, 2015, New Mountain Capital communicated that the $20.05 per share offer price was New Mountain Capital's \"best and final\" offer. New Mountain Capital also indicated a willingness to work expeditiously towards the signing of a definitive merger agreement by April 15, 2015 and requested an extension of its exclusivity period through that date. Subsequently, on March 15, 2015, New Mountain Capital indicated that it would accelerate its due diligence process and requested that the exclusivity period be extended through April 7, 2015.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "March 13, 2015", "normalized": "2015-03-13", "precision": "exact_day"}, {"raw_text": "April 15, 2015", "normalized": "2015-04-15", "precision": "exact_day"}, {"raw_text": "March 15, 2015", "normalized": "2015-03-15", "precision": "exact_day"}, {"raw_text": "April 7, 2015", "normalized": "2015-04-07", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "NEW MOUNTAIN CAPITAL", "entity_type": "acquirer"}], "evidence_density": 4, "temporal_phase": "outcome"}
93:{"block_id": "B093", "document_id": "0001047469-15-004989", "ordinal": 93, "start_line": 1986, "end_line": 1992, "raw_text": "March 16, 2015, our board of directors met, together with representatives of BofA Merrill Lynch and King & Spalding, to discuss the status of the discussions with New\nMountain Capital. At this meeting, at the request of our board of directors, representatives of BofA Merrill Lynch, reviewed and discussed with our board of directors, on a preliminary basis, certain\nfinancial matters. Our board of directors also discussed our recent financial performance and our business on a standalone basis, including the opportunities, risks and capital investment associated\nwith transforming our supply chain. Our board of directors also reviewed the progress with New Mountain Capital and the recent discussions with New Mountain Capital, including New Mountain Capital's\nrequest to extend the exclusivity period. After further discussion, based upon progress in negotiations with New Mountain Capital and New Mountain Capital's reiteration that any definitive merger\nagreement would contain a \"go-shop\" provision, our board of directors authorized an extension of exclusivity with New Mountain Capital through April 7, 2015, which extension letter was signed\non March 18, 2015.", "clean_text": "March 16, 2015, our board of directors met, together with representatives of BofA Merrill Lynch and King & Spalding, to discuss the status of the discussions with New Mountain Capital. At this meeting, at the request of our board of directors, representatives of BofA Merrill Lynch, reviewed and discussed with our board of directors, on a preliminary basis, certain financial matters. Our board of directors also discussed our recent financial performance and our business on a standalone basis, including the opportunities, risks and capital investment associated with transforming our supply chain. Our board of directors also reviewed the progress with New Mountain Capital and the recent discussions with New Mountain Capital, including New Mountain Capital's request to extend the exclusivity period. After further discussion, based upon progress in negotiations with New Mountain Capital and New Mountain Capital's reiteration that any definitive merger agreement would contain a \"go-shop\" provision, our board of directors authorized an extension of exclusivity with New Mountain Capital through April 7, 2015, which extension letter was signed on March 18, 2015.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "March 16, 2015", "normalized": "2015-03-16", "precision": "exact_day"}, {"raw_text": "April 7, 2015", "normalized": "2015-04-07", "precision": "exact_day"}, {"raw_text": "March 18, 2015", "normalized": "2015-03-18", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "NEW MOUNTAIN CAPITAL", "entity_type": "acquirer"}], "evidence_density": 4, "temporal_phase": "outcome"}
95:{"block_id": "B095", "document_id": "0001047469-15-004989", "ordinal": 95, "start_line": 1995, "end_line": 1997, "raw_text": "March 18, 2015, a draft merger agreement was delivered to New Mountain Capital and its advisors. The draft merger agreement included, among other terms, a \"go-shop\" provision\npermitting us to solicit alternative acquisition proposals for sixty days after signing the merger agreement, and the draft\nagreement permitted us to terminate the merger agreement in order to accept a superior offer from another potential buyer.", "clean_text": "March 18, 2015, a draft merger agreement was delivered to New Mountain Capital and its advisors. The draft merger agreement included, among other terms, a \"go-shop\" provision permitting us to solicit alternative acquisition proposals for sixty days after signing the merger agreement, and the draft agreement permitted us to terminate the merger agreement in order to accept a superior offer from another potential buyer.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "March 18, 2015", "normalized": "2015-03-18", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "NEW MOUNTAIN CAPITAL", "entity_type": "acquirer"}], "evidence_density": 4, "temporal_phase": "outcome"}
97:{"block_id": "B097", "document_id": "0001047469-15-004989", "ordinal": 97, "start_line": 2000, "end_line": 2001, "raw_text": "March 24, 2015, our board of directors reviewed again the opportunities, risks and investment associated with transforming our supply chain. After further discussion, our board\nof directors determined not to proceed with an investment in a supply chain transformation project due to", "clean_text": "March 24, 2015, our board of directors reviewed again the opportunities, risks and investment associated with transforming our supply chain. After further discussion, our board of directors determined not to proceed with an investment in a supply chain transformation project due to", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "March 24, 2015", "normalized": "2015-03-24", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [], "evidence_density": 0, "temporal_phase": "outcome"}
99:{"block_id": "B099", "document_id": "0001047469-15-004989", "ordinal": 99, "start_line": 2006, "end_line": 2007, "raw_text": "execution\nrisk and resource constraints, and decided to continue discussions with New Mountain Capital.", "clean_text": "execution risk and resource constraints, and decided to continue discussions with New Mountain Capital.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "NEW MOUNTAIN CAPITAL", "entity_type": "acquirer"}], "evidence_density": 0, "temporal_phase": "outcome"}
101:{"block_id": "B101", "document_id": "0001047469-15-004989", "ordinal": 101, "start_line": 2010, "end_line": 2014, "raw_text": "March 29, 2015, we received a revised draft of the merger agreement from New Mountain Capital. Among other things, the revised merger agreement reduced the \"go-shop\" period\nfrom sixty days to thirty days. During the week of March 30, 2015, we engaged in a series of negotiations with New Mountain Capital and its advisors regarding the provisions the merger\nagreement, including negotiations regarding the terms of the \"go-shop\" and \"no-shop\" provisions (including the length of the \"go-shop\" period), our ability to consider alternative proposals, the size\nof the termination fees and circumstances under which termination fees would be payable, representations and warranties, pre-closing conduct of business covenants, and conditions to closing. In\naddition, we negotiated the terms of other agreements relating to the proposed transaction, including the debt commitment letter, equity commitment letter and limited guaranty.", "clean_text": "March 29, 2015, we received a revised draft of the merger agreement from New Mountain Capital. Among other things, the revised merger agreement reduced the \"go-shop\" period from sixty days to thirty days. During the week of March 30, 2015, we engaged in a series of negotiations with New Mountain Capital and its advisors regarding the provisions the merger agreement, including negotiations regarding the terms of the \"go-shop\" and \"no-shop\" provisions (including the length of the \"go-shop\" period), our ability to consider alternative proposals, the size of the termination fees and circumstances under which termination fees would be payable, representations and warranties, pre-closing conduct of business covenants, and conditions to closing. In addition, we negotiated the terms of other agreements relating to the proposed transaction, including the debt commitment letter, equity commitment letter and limited guaranty.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "March 29, 2015", "normalized": "2015-03-29", "precision": "exact_day"}, {"raw_text": "March 30, 2015", "normalized": "2015-03-30", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "NEW MOUNTAIN CAPITAL", "entity_type": "acquirer"}], "evidence_density": 4, "temporal_phase": "outcome"}
103:{"block_id": "B103", "document_id": "0001047469-15-004989", "ordinal": 103, "start_line": 2017, "end_line": 2019, "raw_text": "negotiations of the merger agreement continued into April, at the direction of our board of directors, both Mr. Morgan and representatives of BofA Merrill Lynch separately\napproached New Mountain Capital in an effort to negotiate an increase in the $20.05 per share offer price. New Mountain Capital reiterated its previous position that the $20.05 per share price offer\nwas New Mountain Capital's \"best and final\" offer.", "clean_text": "negotiations of the merger agreement continued into April, at the direction of our board of directors, both Mr. Morgan and representatives of BofA Merrill Lynch separately approached New Mountain Capital in an effort to negotiate an increase in the $20.05 per share offer price. New Mountain Capital reiterated its previous position that the $20.05 per share price offer was New Mountain Capital's \"best and final\" offer.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "April", "normalized": null, "precision": "unknown"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "NEW MOUNTAIN CAPITAL", "entity_type": "acquirer"}], "evidence_density": 5, "temporal_phase": "outcome"}
104:{"block_id": "B104", "document_id": "0001047469-15-004989", "ordinal": 104, "start_line": 2021, "end_line": 2031, "raw_text": "On April 6, 2015, our board of directors met, together with members of the Company's management and representatives of BofA Merrill Lynch and King & Spalding, to consider\nthe proposed transaction with New Mountain Capital. At this meeting, at the request of our board of directors, representatives of BofA Merrill Lynch reviewed and discussed with our board of directors\ncertain financial matters, including the financial analyses of the merger consideration. The board of directors considered these financial matters with reference to the price proposed by New Mountain\nCapital in connection with the proposed transaction. In so doing, our board of directors took into account its understanding that New Mountain Capital's offer price of $20.05 per share was, in fact,\nthe highest and best price New Mountain Capital was willing to pay for the Company. In addition, representatives of King & Spalding reviewed the terms of the draft merger agreement and other\ntransaction documents, including the debt and equity commitment letters relating to the proposed transaction. In connection with this review,\nKing & Spalding discussed with the board remaining open issues in the merger agreement, including the terms of the \"go-shop\" provision and the size of the termination fees. Our board of\ndirectors was advised that New Mountain Capital continued to insist on a thirty day \"go-shop\" period, a go-shop termination fee of $10 million, a termination fee following the end of the\ngo-shop period of $20 million and a reverse termination fee payable by New Mountain Capital of $30 million. Our board of directors engaged in discussions regarding the materials\npresented at the meeting and the proposed transaction. At the end of the meeting, our board of directors instructed the Company's advisors to proceed to finalize the merger agreement on as favorable\nterms as possible to the Company.", "clean_text": "On April 6, 2015, our board of directors met, together with members of the Company's management and representatives of BofA Merrill Lynch and King & Spalding, to consider the proposed transaction with New Mountain Capital. At this meeting, at the request of our board of directors, representatives of BofA Merrill Lynch reviewed and discussed with our board of directors certain financial matters, including the financial analyses of the merger consideration. The board of directors considered these financial matters with reference to the price proposed by New Mountain Capital in connection with the proposed transaction. In so doing, our board of directors took into account its understanding that New Mountain Capital's offer price of $20.05 per share was, in fact, the highest and best price New Mountain Capital was willing to pay for the Company. In addition, representatives of King & Spalding reviewed the terms of the draft merger agreement and other transaction documents, including the debt and equity commitment letters relating to the proposed transaction. In connection with this review, King & Spalding discussed with the board remaining open issues in the merger agreement, including the terms of the \"go-shop\" provision and the size of the termination fees. Our board of directors was advised that New Mountain Capital continued to insist on a thirty day \"go-shop\" period, a go-shop termination fee of $10 million, a termination fee following the end of the go-shop period of $20 million and a reverse termination fee payable by New Mountain Capital of $30 million. Our board of directors engaged in discussions regarding the materials presented at the meeting and the proposed transaction. At the end of the meeting, our board of directors instructed the Company's advisors to proceed to finalize the merger agreement on as favorable terms as possible to the Company.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "April 6, 2015", "normalized": "2015-04-06", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "NEW MOUNTAIN CAPITAL", "entity_type": "acquirer"}, {"raw_text": "the Company", "entity_type": "party_alias"}, {"raw_text": "The board", "entity_type": "party_alias"}], "evidence_density": 5, "temporal_phase": "outcome"}
106:{"block_id": "B106", "document_id": "0001047469-15-004989", "ordinal": 106, "start_line": 2034, "end_line": 2038, "raw_text": "the April 6, 2015 board meeting, representatives of King & Spalding continued to negotiate the final terms of the merger agreement with New Mountain Capital's\nadvisors. New Mountain Capital expressed its willingness to agree to the Company's proposal that the go-shop termination fee be limited to $8.75 million, that the termination fee following the\nend of the go-shop period be limited to $17.5 million and that the reverse termination fee payable by New Mountain Capital be $33.75 million. However, although New Mountain Capital was\nwilling to provide additional time following the go-shop period to permit the Company to negotiate with respect to potential superior proposals arising during the go-shop period, New Mountain Capital\ninsisted that it was unwilling to increase the length of the go-shop period beyond thirty days.", "clean_text": "the April 6, 2015 board meeting, representatives of King & Spalding continued to negotiate the final terms of the merger agreement with New Mountain Capital's advisors. New Mountain Capital expressed its willingness to agree to the Company's proposal that the go-shop termination fee be limited to $8.75 million, that the termination fee following the end of the go-shop period be limited to $17.5 million and that the reverse termination fee payable by New Mountain Capital be $33.75 million. However, although New Mountain Capital was willing to provide additional time following the go-shop period to permit the Company to negotiate with respect to potential superior proposals arising during the go-shop period, New Mountain Capital insisted that it was unwilling to increase the length of the go-shop period beyond thirty days.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "April 6, 2015", "normalized": "2015-04-06", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "NEW MOUNTAIN CAPITAL", "entity_type": "acquirer"}, {"raw_text": "the Company", "entity_type": "party_alias"}], "evidence_density": 5, "temporal_phase": "outcome"}
108:{"block_id": "B108", "document_id": "0001047469-15-004989", "ordinal": 108, "start_line": 2041, "end_line": 2042, "raw_text": "April 7, 2015, our board of directors met again, together with members of the Company's management and representatives of BofA Merrill Lynch and King & Spalding, to\ndiscuss and review the transaction documents and to consider approval of the proposed transaction with New Mountain", "clean_text": "April 7, 2015, our board of directors met again, together with members of the Company's management and representatives of BofA Merrill Lynch and King & Spalding, to discuss and review the transaction documents and to consider approval of the proposed transaction with New Mountain", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "April 7, 2015", "normalized": "2015-04-07", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "the Company", "entity_type": "party_alias"}], "evidence_density": 2, "temporal_phase": "bidding"}
111:{"block_id": "B111", "document_id": "0001047469-15-004989", "ordinal": 111, "start_line": 2048, "end_line": 2057, "raw_text": "Representatives of King & Spalding reviewed the key provisions of the merger agreement, and discussed with our board of directors the negotiations with New Mountain Capital with\nrespect to the key remaining issues, including the length of the \"go-shop\" provision and the size of the termination fees. After taking into account (a) the robust process conducted in the\nfirst half of 2014, (b) the fact that the Company did not receive any acquisition proposals other than from New Mountain Capital since the termination of the 2014 process, (c) the\nability of the Company to promptly initiate a go-shop process especially in view of the prior 2014 process and (d) New Mountain Capital's willingness to agree to the Company's proposals\nregarding the size of the termination fees, our board of directors was willing to accept a thirty day \"go-shop\" period. Also at this meeting, our board of directors reviewed with BofA Merrill Lynch\nthe financial analyses of the merger consideration and BofA Merrill Lynch delivered to our board of directors an oral opinion, which was confirmed by delivery of a written opinion dated\nApril 7, 2015, to the effect that, as of that date and based upon and subject to the assumptions made, procedures followed, factors considered and limitations on the review undertaken, as\ndescribed in its opinion, the merger consideration to be received by our holders of common stock was fair, from a financial point of view, to such holders. Following discussion, our board of directors\nunanimously determined that the merger agreement and the transactions contemplated thereby, including the merger, were advisable and in the best interests of our stockholders and the Company, and our\nboard of directors resolved to recommend that our stockholders approve the adoption of the merger agreement.", "clean_text": "Representatives of King & Spalding reviewed the key provisions of the merger agreement, and discussed with our board of directors the negotiations with New Mountain Capital with respect to the key remaining issues, including the length of the \"go-shop\" provision and the size of the termination fees. After taking into account (a) the robust process conducted in the first half of 2014, (b) the fact that the Company did not receive any acquisition proposals other than from New Mountain Capital since the termination of the 2014 process, (c) the ability of the Company to promptly initiate a go-shop process especially in view of the prior 2014 process and (d) New Mountain Capital's willingness to agree to the Company's proposals regarding the size of the termination fees, our board of directors was willing to accept a thirty day \"go-shop\" period. Also at this meeting, our board of directors reviewed with BofA Merrill Lynch the financial analyses of the merger consideration and BofA Merrill Lynch delivered to our board of directors an oral opinion, which was confirmed by delivery of a written opinion dated April 7, 2015, to the effect that, as of that date and based upon and subject to the assumptions made, procedures followed, factors considered and limitations on the review undertaken, as described in its opinion, the merger consideration to be received by our holders of common stock was fair, from a financial point of view, to such holders. Following discussion, our board of directors unanimously determined that the merger agreement and the transactions contemplated thereby, including the merger, were advisable and in the best interests of our stockholders and the Company, and our board of directors resolved to recommend that our stockholders approve the adoption of the merger agreement.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "April 7, 2015", "normalized": "2015-04-07", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [{"raw_text": "NEW MOUNTAIN CAPITAL", "entity_type": "acquirer"}, {"raw_text": "the Company", "entity_type": "party_alias"}], "evidence_density": 4, "temporal_phase": "outcome"}
113:{"block_id": "B113", "document_id": "0001047469-15-004989", "ordinal": 113, "start_line": 2060, "end_line": 2061, "raw_text": "the meeting of our board of directors, the parties executed the merger agreement and the related transaction documents and issued a press release announcing the transaction on\nthe morning of April 8, 2015.", "clean_text": "the meeting of our board of directors, the parties executed the merger agreement and the related transaction documents and issued a press release announcing the transaction on the morning of April 8, 2015.", "is_heading": false, "page_break_before": false, "page_break_after": false, "date_mentions": [{"raw_text": "April 8, 2015", "normalized": "2015-04-08", "precision": "exact_day"}], "entity_mentions": [], "evidence_density": 2, "temporal_phase": "outcome"}
